# Backend Architecture

Stack: FastAPI, SQLAlchemy, Alembic, PostgreSQL, Qdrant.

Pattern: **Service + Repository** (similar to NestJS/Express with an isolated data layer).

## Design principles

- **RAG is infrastructure for knowledge** — ingest and search live in `rag/`; no agent or HTTP logic.
- **Document corpus is external data** — PDFs live in repo-root `rag-docs/`; agents never read that folder.
- **Ingest is manual and offline** — run via CLI only; not on Docker build or container startup.
- **Tools expose capabilities** — reusable, independent of any single agent.
- **Agents compose capabilities** — prompts + LLM loop + assigned tools via registry.
- **Services own HTTP/domain transactions** — chat, users, audit; they do not touch Qdrant directly.

