### Core module

Infrastructure only — config, DB session, JWT, Qdrant client, LLM adapters (`core/llm/`). No business rules.

### API layer

Each feature folder: `routes.py` + `schemas.py` (auth also has `dependencies.py`). Routes delegate to `services/` only — no Qdrant, no RAG, no agent logic in handlers.

Features: `auth`, `users`, `chat`, `audit`, `health` — all under `/api/v1/`.

### Repositories

One `*_repository.py` per entity; queries only (no business rules). Postgres for relational data; `vector_repository.py` (planned) for all Qdrant access.

Services instantiate repos in `__init__`; routes never touch repos directly.

### Services

Domain orchestration and transactions: `user`, `chat`, `audit_log`, `health`. Chat service wires the support agent; none of them read `rag-docs/` or Qdrant vectors directly.

### Ingest CLI

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| `scripts/ingest_documents.py` (planned) | Parse CLI args; call `RagService.ingest_directory(settings.resolved_documents_dir)` |

Run manually — not invoked from `docker-entrypoint.sh` or Docker build:

```bash
cd backend && python -m app.scripts.ingest_documents
docker compose exec backend python -m app.scripts.ingest_documents
```

### Scaling folders (when needed)

Keep flat while small (< 5 files per package). Split only when hard to scan:

```
tools/
├── registry.py
├── search_documents.py
└── support/
    └── create_ticket.py        # when 4–5+ tools or distinct domains

agents/
├── registry.py
└── support/
    ├── agent.py
    └── prompts.py              # when multiple agents with different loops
```

## Layer responsibilities

| Layer | Responsibility | Depends on |
|-------|----------------|------------|
| `api/v1/<feature>/` | Routes + schemas (thin) | `services` |
| `models/` | ORM table/relationship definitions | `core/database` |
| `repositories/` | Queries and persistence (Postgres, Qdrant) | `models`, `core/` |
| `rag/` | Load → chunk → embed → search | `rag/embeddings`, `repositories/vector_repository` |
| `tools/` | Callable capabilities exposed to agents | `rag/service` (and others as needed) |
| `agents/` | Prompts, LLM loop, tool orchestration | `core/llm`, `tools/registry` |
| `services/` | Business rules, transactions, orchestration | `repositories`, `agents` |
| `core/llm/` | LLM vendor adapters (chat) | env vars |
| `core/` | Config, DB, Qdrant client, security | env vars |

### Dependency direction

```
api/ → services/ → agents/ → tools/ → rag/ → repositories/ → core/
```

- Agents **must not** import `rag/` or `repositories/vector_repository` directly.
- Tools **must not** import agents.
- `rag/service.py` **must not** import agents or tools.

## RAG module

Single entry point: `rag/service.py` (`RagService`).

| Method | Purpose |
|--------|---------|
| `ingest_directory(path)` | Index all PDFs in a folder |
| `ingest_file(path)` | Index a single document |
| `search(query, top_k)` | Return ranked chunks with metadata |

Ingest is **manual only** via `python -m app.scripts.ingest_documents` — not on Docker build, not in `docker-entrypoint.sh`, and not via chat HTTP routes unless an admin endpoint is added later.

Only `rag/service.py` and the ingest CLI read `DOCUMENTS_DIR`. Agents reach indexed content through `tools/search_documents` → `RagService.search()` → Qdrant.

`repositories/vector_repository.py` owns all Qdrant operations:

- `ensure_collection(vector_size)`
- `upsert(points)`
- `search(query_vector, top_k, score_threshold)`
- `delete_by_doc_id(doc_id)`

No `rag/retriever.py` — search is consumed via `RagService` and exposed as a tool. Replace temporary `NoOpRetriever` in `agents/registry.py` once `RagService` is implemented.

## Document corpus

| Location | Path | Purpose |
|----------|------|---------|
| Host (repo root) | `rag-docs/` | Place HP PDF files here |
| Docker (backend container) | `/app/rag-docs` | Read-only volume mount of `./rag-docs` |
| Local backend dev | `../rag-docs` (default via `DOCUMENTS_DIR`) | Same folder, resolved from `backend/` |

Env var: `DOCUMENTS_DIR` — optional override; defaults to repo-root `rag-docs/` when unset (see `config.resolved_documents_dir`).

PDFs are **not** copied into the Docker image. Qdrant vectors persist in the `qdrant_data` Compose volume after ingest.

## Tools module

Tools live in `tools/` (not under `agents/`). Each tool is a standalone file; `registry.py` maps names to factories.

```python
# tools/registry.py — wiring only, no business logic
_TOOL_FACTORIES = {
    "search_documents": lambda deps: SearchDocumentsTool(deps.rag),
}

def build_tool_set(names: tuple[str, ...], deps: ToolDeps) -> dict[str, Tool]:
    return {name: _TOOL_FACTORIES[name](deps) for name in names}
```

## Agents module

`agents/registry.py` defines per-agent config:

```python
@dataclass(frozen=True)
class ToolBinding:
    name: str
    invocation: str  # "always" | "on_demand"

@dataclass(frozen=True)
class AgentConfig:
    name: str
    prompt: str
    tools: tuple[ToolBinding, ...]
    loop_mode: str  # "single_shot" | "tool_loop"
```

| Field | Behavior |
|-------|----------|
| `ToolBinding.invocation = "always"` | Tool runs before every LLM call (e.g. `search_documents`) |
| `ToolBinding.invocation = "on_demand"` | Tool exposed to LLM; called only when needed (phase 2) |
| `loop_mode = "single_shot"` | Run `always` tools → one LLM call (phase 1) |
| `loop_mode = "tool_loop"` | Run `always` tools → LLM loop with `on_demand` tools (phase 2) |

`dependencies.py` builds agents via `build_agent("support", get_llm_provider())`.

## Request flow

**Current (chat + LLM + SSE):**

```
Client → api/v1/chat (SSE) → ChatService.process_message_stream → repositories → PostgreSQL
                              ↘ agents/support_agent.reply_stream → core/llm/
                                                                    ↘ tools/ (search_documents)
```

See `.cursor/rules/chat-sse-streaming.mdc` and `docs/chat-sse-streaming.md`.

**Legacy diagram (RAG pending):**

```
Client → api/v1/chat → ChatService → repositories → PostgreSQL
                              ↘ agents/support_agent → core/llm/
                                                       ↘ tools/ (NoOp / search_documents)
```

**Target (full RAG):**

```
Client → api/v1/chat → ChatService → repositories → PostgreSQL
                              ↘ agents/support_agent
                                    ↘ tools/search_documents
                                          ↘ rag/service
                                                ↘ repositories/vector_repository → Qdrant
                                    ↘ core/llm/ (chat)
```

**Ingest (offline, manual):**

```
rag-docs/*.pdf
  → CLI: python -m app.scripts.ingest_documents
  → rag/service.ingest_directory(DOCUMENTS_DIR)
  → load → chunk → embed → vector_repository.upsert
  → Qdrant
```

**Search (online, chat):**

```
User message → agents/support_agent → tools/search_documents
  → RagService.search() → vector_repository → Qdrant
  → LLM (context from retrieved chunks only; no direct file access)
```

## LLM and embedding providers

Vendor adapters implement a common interface — no prompts, tool calling, or business rules.

| Type | Location | Status |
|------|----------|--------|
| LLM chat | `core/llm/` | OpenAI implemented |
| Embeddings | `rag/embeddings/` | OpenAI implemented |

Env vars: `LLM_PROVIDER`, `LLM_MODEL`, `OPENAI_API_KEY`, `EMBEDDING_PROVIDER`, `EMBEDDING_MODEL`, `QDRANT_COLLECTION`, `DOCUMENTS_DIR` (see `.env.example`).

`get_db` lives in `core/database.py`. Services instantiate repos — routes only pass the session.

## Design rules

1. Thin routes — no business logic in `api/`
2. Each feature in its own folder — `api/v1/<feature>/routes.py` + `schemas.py`
3. `api/v1/router.py` centralizes and registers all features
4. Services instantiate repos in `__init__` — repos concentrate data access
5. Services must not run queries directly — always via `repositories/`
6. Transactions in `services/` — commit/rollback do not belong in routes
7. `models/` only defines ORM schema; queries live in repos
8. Versioned routes — prefix `/api/v1/` via central router
9. Tools are independent of agents — assign via `agents/registry.py`
10. RAG logic stays in `rag/` — agents reach it only through tools

## Testing

Stack: **pytest**, **pytest-cov**, **httpx** (`requirements-dev.txt` — local/CI only, not in the Docker image).

| Type | Location | What to test |
|------|----------|--------------|
| Unit | `tests/unit/` | Services, rag, tools, agents — mocked repos/clients |
| API | `tests/api/` | Routes, status codes, JSON via `TestClient` |
| Integration (later) | `tests/integration/` | Real Postgres / Qdrant when needed |

Run with in-memory SQLite (`conftest.py` overrides `get_db`). Coverage policy: see `test-coverage.mdc` (≥ 95% on `app/`; 100% on `services/` and `repositories/`).

## Where to put new code

| What | Where |
|------|-------|
| New HTTP feature | `api/v1/<feature>/routes.py` + register in `router.py` |
| Feature DTOs | `api/v1/<feature>/schemas.py` |
| DB table | `models/<entity>.py` + Alembic migration |
| Postgres query/persistence | `repositories/<entity>_repository.py` |
| Qdrant operations | `repositories/vector_repository.py` |
| Domain business rule | `services/<domain>_service.py` |
| LLM adapter (chat) | `core/llm/<vendor>.py` + register in `factory.py` |
| Embedding adapter | `rag/embeddings/<vendor>.py` + register in `factory.py` |
| PDF loader / chunking | `rag/loaders/`, `rag/chunking.py` |
| RAG ingest + search | `rag/service.py` |
| New tool | `tools/<tool_name>.py` + register in `tools/registry.py` |
| New agent | `agents/<name>_agent.py` + register in `agents/registry.py` |
| Agent prompt | `agents/prompts.py` or `agents/<name>/prompts.py` when split |
| Ingest CLI | `app/scripts/ingest_documents.py` |
| Unit test | `tests/unit/<layer>/test_<module>.py` |
| API test | `tests/api/test_<feature>.py` |
